**Explanation:**

The code defines several API endpoints using the Flask framework.  Each `@admin_api.route()` decorator defines a route (path) and associates it with a handler function.  The output above extracts these routes and their associated handlers.

*   **`/users`**: Maps to the `get_admin_users` function.
*   **`/user/{uid}/password`**: Maps to the `change_user_password` function.  The `{uid}` indicates a path parameter.
*   **`/user/{uid}`**: Maps to the `delete_user` function.  The `{uid}` indicates a path parameter.
*   **`/user/{uid}`**: Maps to the `update_user` function.  The `{uid}` indicates a path parameter.
*   **`/group/all`**: Maps to the `get_all_group` function.
*   **`/group/{gid}`**: Maps to the `get_group` function. The `{gid}` indicates a path parameter.
*   **`/group`**: Maps to the `create_group` function.
*   **`/group/{gid}`**: Maps to the `update_group` function. The `{gid}` indicates a path parameter.
*   **`/group/{gid}`**: Maps to the `delete_group` function. The `{gid}` indicates a path parameter.
*   **`/permission/dispatch/batch`**: Maps to the `dispatch_auths` function.
*   **`/permission/remove`**: Maps to the `remove_auths` function.

All paths are extracted from literal strings within the `@admin_api.route()` decorators.  All handlers are functions defined within the same file.  All entries are considered RESTful APIs.  None of the entries are explicitly marked as for testing purposes.

path.description: The HTTP request path, which must begin with a forward slash (/) and have path parameters wrapped in curly braces ({}). Set this to null if it cannot be determined.

handler.description: The function, class, class method, or object that handles the HTTP request. Use exactly "anonymous" to denote an anonymous implementation.
handler.title: Handler

handler_in_same_file.description: Whether the handler's implementation is present in the same source code file, rather than being imported.
handler_in_same_file.title: Handler In Same File

path_is_prefix.description: Whether the path string is a prefix rather than a full path.
path_is_prefix.title: Path Is Prefix

path_from_string_literal.description: Whether the path string is extracted from a literal string defined in the source code.
path_from_string_literal.title: Path From String Literal

path_from_naming_convention.description: Whether the path string is derived from a naming convention supported by the framework.
path_from_naming_convention.title: Path From Naming Convention

is_restful_api.description: Whether the API entry is for a RESTful API, rather than other types of APIs.
